Document: SkeletonModificationStack2D
Path: godot/classes/class_skeletonmodificationstack2d.rst
Summary: A node that allows to apply modifications to a Skeleton2D.

Inherits: Node2D < CanvasItem < Node2D < Object

SkeletonModificationStack2D

A node that allows to apply modifications to a Skeleton2D.

This node is a child of Skeleton2D and allows to apply modifications to the bones of the skeleton. The modifications are applied in the order they appear in the stack.

Each modification is a separate node that inherits from SkeletonModification2D.

Available modifications:

*   SkeletonModification2DLookAt
*   SkeletonModification2DIK2D
*   SkeletonModification2DChainIK2D
*   SkeletonModification2DTwoBoneIK2D
*   SkeletonModification2DTransform
*   SkeletonModification2DFreeze
*   SkeletonModification2DRotate
*   SkeletonModification2DSpring

You can create your own modifications by creating a script that inherits from SkeletonModification2D.

The modifications are applied in the order they appear in the stack. This means that the output of one modification can be the input of the next one.

The SkeletonModificationStack2D node itself does not have any properties or methods that you need to configure. You just need to add the modification nodes as children of this node.

The Skeleton2D node will automatically find its SkeletonModificationStack2D child and apply the modifications in the correct order.
